Global logos are only displayed in Dashboard, not on any pages. Tested all themes, image would not display at all with _Default, Classic and Left Hand Navigation_ themes. _Clickr_ theme worked once, however would not display at all after uploading replacement image.

Global logo files also take a while to appear in Dashboard. Old logo will continue to be shown despite being replaced by new file in Resources folder instantaneously.
Loading a few new pages (roughly a minute or so after upload) seems to fix this, as will a reboot of Confluence.

A patch for Confluence 2.8 is now available for this bug:
{panel:title=patch instructions}
Place the attached -ConfluenceBandanaPersister.class- ConfluenceDaoBandanaPersister.class into 
{noformat}
<confluence install root>/confluence/WEB-INF/classes/com/atlassian/confluence/setup/bandana
{noformat}
You may have to create the bandana subdirectory.
Then restart Confluence.
{panel}

